<body>
    <h1>Instructions For Club Owners</h1>

    <h2>Set Up A Club Calendar</h2>
    <p>What fun a club be without get-togethers? Here are some instructions to set up a calendar for your club's events.</p>
    
    <ol>
        <li>If you do not yet have an account with Google, we ask that you please create one.</li>
        <li>After logging into your account, please access Google Calendar.</li>
        <li>Create a new calendar, and please give it the same name as your book club.</li>
        <li>Ensure that only Your Club Name's Calendar are checked off in the lower section.</li>
        <li>Click the three dots to the right of Your Club Name's Calendar.</li>
        <li>Click on "Settings and sharing".</li>
        <li>Scroll until you see "Access permissions for events". Click the checkbox that says "Make available to public", and make sure the drop down to the right says "See all event details".</li>
        <li>On the left hand panel, click "Integrate Calendar".</li>
        <li>There is a button, "Customize", which will show you what your club members will be able to see. You can edit these as you would like. We recommend keeping the holidays included.</li>
        <li>At the top, there is a link called "Embed code". Highlight the portion that is within the quotation mark. You will need to copy and paste this into the question below.</li>
    </ol>

    <script src="server.js"></script>
</body>

